{"metadata":{"kernelspec":{"name":"ir","display_name":"R","language":"R"},"language_info":{"name":"R","codemirror_mode":"r","pygments_lexer":"r","mimetype":"text/x-r-source","file_extension":".r","version":"4.4.0"},"kaggle":{"accelerator":"none","dataSources":[{"sourceId":11116340,"sourceType":"datasetVersion","datasetId":6931283}],"dockerImageVersionId":30749,"isInternetEnabled":true,"language":"r","sourceType":"notebook","isGpuEnabled":false}},"nbformat_minor":4,"nbformat":4,"cells":[{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"![](https://i0.wp.com/blog.dsacademy.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/A-Linguagem-R-Continua-Crescendo-em-Popularidade.jpg?w=1200&ssl=1)","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Introduction\n\nR is a programming language and software environment primarily used for statistical computing, data analysis, and visualization. R is widely used by statisticians, data analysts, researchers, and data scientists, especially in academic and healthcare settings. Some of the Key Features of R and Common Use Cases are the the following:\n\n## Key Features of R:\n\n- Statistical Analysis: R includes a wide variety of statistical techniques like linear and nonlinear modeling, time-series analysis, classification, clustering, etc.\n\n- Data Visualization: R has powerful libraries such as ggplot2 and plotly for creating high-quality, customizable visualizations.\n\n- Data Handling: R is excellent for handling and manipulating large datasets using packages like dplyr, tidyr, and data.table.\n\n- Open Source: R is free and open-source, with a large community that continuously contributes packages and updates.\n\n- Extensible: Users can create their own functions and packages, or use thousands of packages available via CRAN (Comprehensive R Archive Network).\n\n## Common Use Cases:\n\n- Data analysis and reporting\n\n- Statistical modeling\n\n- Machine learning\n\n- Data visualization and dashboards\n\n- Bioinformatics and epidemiology\n\n- -----------","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# Table of Contents\n\n- R Basic Syntax: \n- Basic Operations: \n- Control Flow: \n- Functions: \n- Data Structures: \n- Reading & Writing Data: \n- Plotting: \n- Packages: ","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"------------------\n# ðŸ“¦ R Basics Syntax","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### âž¤ Variables","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"x <- 10      # assign 10 to x\ny <- 5\nname <- \"John\"","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### âž¤ Data Types","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"num <- 3.14         # Numeric\ntext <- \"Hello\"     # Character\nflag <- TRUE        # Logical","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### âž¤ Vectors","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"v <- c(1, 2, 3, 4)   # Combine elements into a vector","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"---------------------\n# ðŸ”¹ Basic Operations  ","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"x + y      # Addition\nx * y      # Multiplication\nx > y      # Logical comparison\nmean(v)    # Average of vector\nsum(v)     # Sum","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"-----------------\n# ðŸ”„ Control Flow","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### âž¤ If Statements","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"if (x > y) {\n  print(\"x is greater\")\n}","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### âž¤ For Loop","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"for (i in 1:5) {\n  print(i)\n}","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"-------------\n# ðŸ§® Functions","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"add <- function(a, b) {\n  return(a + b)\n}\n\nadd(3, 4)   # Returns 7","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"---------------\n# ðŸ“Š Data Structures in R","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### âž¤ Vectors","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"v <- c(10, 20, 30)","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### âž¤ Data Frames","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"df <- data.frame(Name=c(\"Tom\", \"Jane\"), Age=c(30, 25))","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### âž¤ Lists","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"lst <- list(name=\"Alice\", age=25)","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### âž¤ Matrix","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"m <- matrix(1:6, nrow=2, ncol=3)","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"-----------\n# ðŸ“‚ Reading & Writing Data","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### âž¤ Read CSV","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"data <- read.csv(\"file.csv\")","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### âž¤ Write CSV","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"write.csv(df, \"output.csv\")","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"-----------\n# ðŸ“ˆ Plotting","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### âž¤ Basic Plot","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"x <- c(1, 2, 3)\ny <- c(2, 4, 6)\nplot(x, y, type=\"b\", col=\"blue\", main=\"Simple Plot\")","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"execution_failed":"2025-04-10T21:13:40.677Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### âž¤ Advanced Plot with ggplot2","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"install.packages(\"ggplot2\")\nlibrary(ggplot2)\n\nggplot(data=students, aes(x=Name, y=Age)) +\n  geom_bar(stat=\"identity\")","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"execution_failed":"2025-04-10T21:13:40.677Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"-----------\n# ðŸ“š Useful Functions\n\n- summary() â€“ Summary statistics\n\n- str() â€“ Structure of object\n\n- head() / tail() â€“ Preview data\n\n- length() â€“ Number of elements\n\n- class() â€“ Data type of object","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"---------------\n# ðŸ§° Managing Packages","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"install.packages(\"ggplot2\")    # Install\nlibrary(ggplot2)               # Load\n\nggplot(data=df, aes(x=Name, y=Age)) + \n  geom_bar(stat=\"identity\")\n","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"execution_failed":"2025-04-10T21:13:40.677Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### Use packages like:\n\n- ggplot2 â€“ Data visualization\n\n- dplyr â€“ Data manipulation\n\n- tidyr â€“ Data tidying\n\n- readr â€“ Fast file reading","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"-----------\n# âœ… Next Steps\n- Practice with small projects (e.g., analyze a CSV file).\n- Resources like: Kaggle or DataCamp, can provide datasets for small projects.","metadata":{}}]}